Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on video surveillance applications and proposes a hybrid tracking algorithm for object detection and tracking using AI and ML algorithms. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper mentions the use of Machine Learning algorithms for object detection and tracking. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an AI-based approach for smart surveillance. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper mentions the importance of on-site or near-site data mining for time-sensitive and data-intensive video surveillance applications, which may require security measures. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the use of edge computing to push the boundaries of cloud computing and enable intelligent surveillance as an edge service.
